<Rewrite PAsource="" >Accusing him earlier of </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >lying </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >constantly to </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >the jury, Mr Carman said: "</Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >If you can forgive the phrase, </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >you are a goalkeeper who keeps moving the goalposts in the sense that you are playing with the truth in the witness box and trimming your answers to fit in with any new facts presented to you."
</Verbatim>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >Mr Carman said: "I have to suggest to you your whole story is riddled with lies, evasion and deviousness."
</Verbatim>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >Mr Grobbelaar replied: "That is simply not true."
</Verbatim>

